abstract: The group, the Democratic Majority for Israel, will begin airing a negative campaign spot on Wednesday, as worries mount among moderate Democrats that Mr. Sanders could win the Iowa caucuses.
snippet: The group, the Democratic Majority for Israel, will begin airing a negative campaign spot on Wednesday, as worries mount among moderate Democrats that Mr. Sanders could win the Iowa caucuses.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — A Democratic super PAC will begin airing attack ads in Iowa against Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont on Wednesday, marking the first time a Democratic organization has run a negative campaign spot targeting Mr. Sanders by name in either of his two primary campaigns.

headline_main: Pompeo’s Rage Aimed at Mary Louise Kelly of NPR
headline_print_headline: Pompeo’s Rage Aimed at the NPR Reporter

abstract: The Georgia Republican was sworn in as the Senate’s newest member just in time to sit for the impeachment trial against President Trump.
snippet: The Georgia Republican was sworn in as the Senate’s newest member just in time to sit for the impeachment trial against President Trump.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As her colleagues fretted privately on Monday over revelations from John R. Bolton, the former national security adviser whose forthcoming book pokes holes in President Trump’s impeachment defense, the newest Republican member of the United States Senate rushed to publicly side with Mr. Trump.

abstract: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said his government would effectively annex nearly a third of the occupied West Bank, with U.S. approval.
snippet: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said his government would effectively annex nearly a third of the occupied West Bank, with U.S. approval.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — The only immediate consequence of the Trump peace plan — and possibly all that will ever come of it — was the green light President Trump gave to Israel Tuesday to expand its territory by effectively annexing vast stretches of land it has long coveted on the West Bank.

lead_paragraph: Ben Smith, the editor in chief of BuzzFeed, who built a hard-hitting news operation within a digital media organization better known for clickbait and listicles, will be The New York Times’s next media columnist.

abstract: The Congressional Budget Office sees low interest rates, slow growth and big deficits through 2029.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Congressional Budget Office predicted on Tuesday that the United States deficit will top $1 trillion annually over the next 10 years, ultimately reaching $1.7 trillion in 2030.

abstract: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez. An Olympic curling coach. A host of ‘Queer Eye.’ At house parties and rallies, stand-ins for the candidates hit the trail in Iowa.
snippet: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez. An Olympic curling coach. A host of ‘Queer Eye.’ At house parties and rallies, stand-ins for the candidates hit the trail in Iowa.
lead_paragraph: WEST DES MOINES, Iowa — Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez and the filmmaker Michael Moore held a rally in Iowa City for Bernie Sanders. Amy Klobuchar’s daughter, Abigail Bessler, hosted a “Hotdish House Party” in West Des Moines. And Julián Castro, a former presidential candidate himself, hit the campaign trail for Elizabeth Warren.

headline_main: With Senators Stuck in Washington, Surrogates Get Starring Role in Iowa
headline_print_headline: As Senators Return to Washington, Stand-Ins Become Main Attraction in Iowa

abstract: Despite the Trump administration’s effort to persuade Britain to bar the Chinese technology giant from its new broadband network, Boris Johnson decided to grant Huawei limited access.
snippet: Despite the Trump administration’s effort to persuade Britain to bar the Chinese technology giant from its new broadband network, Boris Johnson decided to grant Huawei limited access.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Since becoming Britain’s prime minister six months ago, Boris Johnson has managed to strike a delicate balance in his relationship with President Trump, keeping him at a distance during Britain’s election while more recently showing sympathy for his pressure tactics against Iran.
